{"title":"Crankbrothers Candy Lace Shoes are Ready for Gravel or XC Adventures","link":"https://bikerumor.com/crankbrothers-candy-lace-gravel-xc-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes/","date":1713186000000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_candies-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel XC adventure mountain bike shoes\" /></p>\n<p>Crankbrothers laces up a new set of Candy Lace shoes, slimmed-down and dialed-back to meet the needs of gravel and XC riders. These latest clipless mountain bike shoes feel like a far departure from the gravity shoes we’re used to seeing from Crankbrothers, but unsurprisingly look like a perfect match to their mini Candy MTB pedals. Perfect for the mixed surface adventures you’re likely to get up to on a Candy pedal, the new Candy Lace shoes are ready for everything from all-road riding, to gravel bikepacking, even to cross-country mountain biking, too. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel and XC adventure biking shoes</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-detail-1536x864.jpg\" alt=\"Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel XC adventure mountain bike shoes, standing on gravel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-detail-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-detail-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-detail-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-detail-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-detail-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-detail.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos by Tanner Stephens/Crankbrothers)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Crankbrothers designed the new Candy Lace with a wider range of off-road cyclists in mind… “for those long, adventurous rides.” It is a simple, slim profile shoe with a tough synthetic upper, hard-to-argue-with laces, a mid-stiffness fiber-reinforced nylon sole for good pedaling, and a lugged rubber outsole for plenty of grip when it comes time to hike-a-bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-riding.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-riding-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel XC adventure mountain bike shoes, riding gravel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-riding-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-riding-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-riding-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-riding-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-riding-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-riding-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_photo-by-Tanner-Stephens_gravel-riding.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Designed to be a perfect match to Candy pedals for all-road, gravel, bikepacking, and cross-country mountain biking adventure rides.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech details</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_outside-in-black.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_outside-in-black-1536x853.jpg\" alt=\"Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel XC adventure mountain bike shoes, outside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_outside-in-black-1536x853.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_outside-in-black-297x165.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_outside-in-black-120x67.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_outside-in-black-768x427.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_outside-in-black.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Candy Lace features a water-resistant synthetic upper built for toughness, with perforations throughout for ventilation. Plus, a polyurethane film overtop to make them easy to keep clean. Then, classic laces for an easily adjustable relaxed fit, plus a loop to keep your bows out of the chain. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_inside.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_inside-1536x853.jpg\" alt=\"Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel XC adventure mountain bike shoes, inside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_inside-1536x853.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_inside-297x165.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_inside-120x67.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_inside-768x427.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_inside.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The shoes also get protection via rubber toe &amp; heel bumpers that wrap up from the sole. But also extra TPU reinforcements fully across the toe and on the outside to resist scrapes from any adventure you undertake. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_sole.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_sole-1536x864.jpg\" alt=\"Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel XC adventure mountain bike shoes, sole\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_sole-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_sole-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_sole-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_sole-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_sole-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_sole.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Crankbrothers doesn’t give a real stiffness rating. But says a fiber-reinforced nylon shank in the shoe promises stiffness “for optimal power transfer on every pedal stroke”.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the bottom, the Candy Lace features a lugged tread design made from “durable MC1 Match” rubber compound developed to “withstand seasons of use” and offer “reliable off-bike traction for wherever your adventure leads”. An extended 35mm long cutout for 2-bolt SPD cleats offers plenty of room for most everyone to get cleat placement perfect for their ideal fit.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_with-Candy-pedals.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1201\" height=\"676\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_with-Candy-pedals.jpg\" alt=\"Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel XC adventure mountain bike shoes, designed for Candy pedals\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_with-Candy-pedals.jpg 1201w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_with-Candy-pedals-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_with-Candy-pedals-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_with-Candy-pedals-768x432.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, the cleat box and mid-shoe tread blocks are perfectly designed for a supportive interface with Crankbrothers Candy pedals. Probably making the Candy Lace the perfect setup for long-distance adventure riders who already use Crankbrothers pedals.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Weight-wise, Crankbrothers claims the Candy Lace tip the scales at 340g (per shoe, size 42).</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Crankbrothers Candy Lace – Pricing, options &amp; availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_color-options.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_color-options-1536x864.jpg\" alt=\"Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel XC adventure mountain bike shoes, black blue or white colorways\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_color-options-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_color-options-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_color-options-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_color-options-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_color-options-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_color-options.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Crankbrothers Candy Lace shoes sell for $160 / 160€ and come in whole EU sizes 35-49, plus half sizes 37-47. Pick your preferred style from three color options. Black on black with a natural gum rubber sole, dark on light blue with a matching blue sole, or white on grey with a grey rubber sole. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_colors-of-candies.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"691\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_colors-of-candies-1536x691.jpg\" alt=\"Crankbrothers Candy Lace gravel XC adventure mountain bike shoes, 2024 colors with candies\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_colors-of-candies-1536x691.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_colors-of-candies-297x134.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_colors-of-candies-120x54.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_colors-of-candies-768x346.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Crankbrothers-Candy-Lace-gravel-XC-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes_colors-of-candies.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Candy Lace shoes are available now both online direct from Crankbrothers, and through your local bikeshop.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.crankbrothers.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Crankbrothers.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/crankbrothers-candy-lace-gravel-xc-adventure-mountain-bike-shoes/\">Crankbrothers Candy Lace Shoes are Ready for Gravel or XC Adventures</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d01fb926b335a62c05ad7f4f0eda0e5df4b946718c7c764c1cb942309d2bbffe","category":"Cycling"}